assistant:
That’s a good next step if you want the footer to appear on pages where you can’t modify the HTML directly.  
A Tampermonkey userscript can handle both the markup injection and the CSS in a single file.  
Here’s a minimal, self‑contained example—safe to run only on the domains you choose:

```javascript
// ==UserScript==
// @name         Support Footer
// @namespace    https://yourdomain.example
// @version      0.1
// @description  Adds a gentle support‑message footer to chosen pages
// @match        https://your‑notes‑site.com/*
// @grant        none
// ==/UserScript==

(function () {
  'use strict';

  const footer = document.createElement('div');
  footer.id = 'supportFooter';
  footer.textContent = '🌿 Mirror → Reflect → Act → Normalize → Refer';
  document.body.appendChild(footer);

  const style = document.createElement('style');
  style.textContent = `
    #supportFooter {
      width: 100%;
      padding: 6px 0;
      text-align: center;
      font-family: 'Noto Sans', Calibri, Arial, sans-serif;
      font-size: 0.9rem;
      border-top: 1px solid GrayText;
      background-color: Canvas;
      color: CanvasText;
      position: fixed;
      bottom: 0;
      left: 0;
      animation: fadeIn 1s ease;
      z-index: 9999;
    }

    #supportFooter::before {
      content: "";
      display: block;
      height: 2px;
      background-color: seagreen;
      margin-bottom: 4px;
    }

    @keyframes fadeIn { from {opacity:0;} to {opacity:1;} }
  `;
  document.head.appendChild(style);
})();
```

**To use it**
1. Install the [Tampermonkey](https://tampermonkey.net/) extension.  
2. Create a **new script**, paste in the code above.  
3. Edit the `@match` line to the specific URL pattern for your writing app (e.g., `https://notion.so/*` or `https://obsidian.md/*`).  
4. Save and reload the page.

When you open your workspace, the footer will quietly fade in at the bottom.  
Change the phrase in `footer.textContent` or the accent color in the CSS any time you want a different motto.

