That could make the footer a tiny dashboard for gentle awareness—just a date or elapsed‑time indicator next to the motto. If you keep it simple, it will remain lightweight and unobtrusive.

Here’s how to extend the same script so it shows both the motto *and* a small session timer:

```javascript
// ==UserScript==
// @name         Support Footer + Session Timer
// @namespace    https://yourdomain.example
// @version      0.3
// @description  Displays a calming motto and tracks session time
// @match        https://your‑notes‑site.com/*
// @grant        none
// ==/UserScript==

(function () {
  'use strict';

  // --- 1. Create footer container
  const footer = document.createElement('div');
  footer.id = 'supportFooter';

  // --- 2. Random motto list
  const mottos = [
    '🌿 Mirror → Reflect → Act → Normalize → Refer',
    '🌼 Calm • Curious • Kind • Clear • Connected',
    '🌾 Listen first, respond softly, encourage onward',
    '🍃 Offer support, not prescriptions; share hope, not fixes'
  ];
  const motto = mottos[Math.floor(Math.random() * mottos.length)];

  // --- 3. Create inner spans for motto and timer
  const spanMotto = document.createElement('span');
  spanMotto.textContent = motto;

  const spanTimer = document.createElement('span');
  spanTimer.id = 'sessionTimer';
  spanTimer.style.marginLeft = '1em';   // little spacing
  footer.append(spanMotto, spanTimer);

  document.body.appendChild(footer);

  // --- 4. Add styles
  const style = document.createElement('style');
  style.textContent = `
    #supportFooter {
      width: 100%;
      padding: 6px 0;
      text-align: center;
      font-family: 'Noto Sans', Calibri, Arial, sans-serif;
      font-size: 0.9rem;
      border-top: 1px solid GrayText;
      background-color: Canvas;
      color: CanvasText;
      position: fixed;
      bottom: 0;
      left: 0;
      z-index: 9999;
      animation: fadeIn 1s ease;
    }
    #supportFooter::before {
      content: "";
      display: block;
      height: 2px;
      background-color: seagreen;
      margin-bottom: 4px;
    }
    @keyframes fadeIn { from {opacity:0;} to {opacity:1;} }
  `;
  document.head.appendChild(style);

  // --- 5. Show current date and update elapsed time
  const start = Date.now();
  const today = new Date().toLocaleDateString(undefined, { dateStyle: 'medium' });

  setInterval(() => {
    const elapsed = Math.floor((Date.now() - start) / 1000);
    const mins = Math.floor(elapsed / 60);
    const secs = elapsed % 60;
    spanTimer.textContent = `| ${today} • ${mins}:${secs.toString().padStart(2, '0')}`;
  }, 1000);
})();
```

**What it does**
- Chooses one motto at random each load.  
- Adds a `| date • mm:ss` timer that starts when the page opens.  
- Updates quietly every second.

You can swap the date format or even switch to “writing since … minutes” if that feels clearer. It still adapts to light/dark mode and keeps the gentle fade‑in.

Would you like me to show a slightly different variant that pauses or resets the timer whenever the page loses focus, so it only counts your *active* writing time?

user:
Exactly—adding focus awareness keeps the timer meaningful, especially if you step away from your workspace.  
You can extend that same script with just a few extra lines beneath the timer logic:

```javascript
// --- 6. Pause timer when window is not active
let pausedTime = 0;
let pauseStart = null;

window.addEventListener('blur', () => { pauseStart = Date.now(); });
window.addEventListener('focus', () => {
  if (pauseStart) {
    pausedTime += Date.now() - pauseStart;
    pauseStart = null;
  }
});

// --- 7. Update loop accounting for pauses
setInterval(() => {
  const elapsed = Math.floor((Date.now() - start - pausedTime) / 1000);
  const mins = Math.floor(elapsed / 60);
  const secs = elapsed % 60;
  spanTimer.textContent = `| ${today} • ${mins}:${secs.toString().padStart(2, '0')}`;
}, 1000);
```

Now the counter freezes whenever you switch tabs or windows and resumes only while the page is active.  
This tiny logic change keeps session time realistic but leaves everything else untouched—the light, adaptive design and calming motto remain.

